                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Regular, by a well-trained hand.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>The handwriting is similar to that of the
                        18th-cent. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12076ZawaldaMaryam">Zawalda Māryām</persName>
                        but cannot be identified with it.<date>18th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>ቡራ፡ for ቡራኬ፡</item>
                           <item>እማ፡ for እማሬ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the reigning monarch; incipits
                           of the texts (sometimes alternately in red and black lines); directives
                           for the ministers; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the
                           Ethiopic numerals; some of the musical notation signs above the lines;
                           some of the abbreviations.
 
 The text on fol. 3r is written
                           alternately in red and black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">A few fragments of the text are written
                        in compressed script (e.g., <locus target="#28rb">28rb</locus>, va, vb;
                        32ra).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
